                    <h2>machines of the wild</h2>
                    <p>In Horizon Zero Dawn, machines are central to both the story and the gameplay. Set in a post-apocalyptic future where nature has reclaimed the earth, these robotic creatures roam the wilds and mimic the behavior of real-world animals. Created originally by the artificial intelligence system known as GAIA, these machines were meant to restore and maintain the planet’s biosphere after a cataclysmic extinction event. However, a mysterious signal later caused many of them to become hostile.</p>
                    <h2>types and behavior</h2>
                    <p>The machines come in various types, each with unique designs, behaviors, and functions. Some are passive and resemble herbivores like deer or cows, while others are aggressive and modeled after predators or military hardware. you can see them al on the other page</p>
